    "text": "Oh this was a good one from last year: <https://blog.nilenso.com/blog/2023/11/10/spreadsheets-and-small-software>\n\nTreesheets is a particularly memorable project in this area: <https://strlen.com/treesheets>\n\n<https://loglo.app> experiments with combining a grid with a shared stack per row.\n\n<https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=y1Ca5czOY7Q> shows off a project called Flowsheets.\n\nA few tantalizing links in rarely-used channels:\n<https://akkartik.name/archives/foc/of-end-user-programming/1573942666.111300.html>\n\n<https://akkartik.name/archives/foc/of-logic-programming/1621430499.000300.html>\n\n<https://akkartik.name/archives/foc/of-music/1625731658.003200.html>\n\nThe history of <#CC2JRGVLK|introduce-yourself> has a _ton_ of references to people trying to do this. Most not active here, sadly: <https://akkartik.name/archives/foc/introduce-yourself>\n\nOther than that, there's just too much, but maybe a good starting point is to search for keywords in the top-level view of these channels:\n<https://akkartik.name/archives/foc/thinking-together>\n<https://akkartik.name/archives/foc/linking-together>\n<https://akkartik.name/archives/foc/share-your-work>\n<https://akkartik.name/archives/foc/present-company>\n<https://akkartik.name/archives/foc/two-minute-week>\n<https://akkartik.name/archives/foc/devlog-together>\n\nJari and others, definitely share any resources you've been collecting as well. Or highlight any nuggets you particularly like in the archives. This feels like a topic worth a public list of curated bookmarks. Maybe somebody already knows of one?",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "thread_ts": "1722699168.955959",
    "parent_user_id": "U07CGRNH6S2",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
